# Sitecore XM Cloud Rules

## For `examples/basic-nextjs` (AI Demo Builder)

All Sitecore rules for the demo builder live in `examples/basic-nextjs/docs/ai/`.
Read and follow those docs — they override everything in this file.

Key entry points:
- `docs/ai/rules/01-sitecore-router.md` — classify the task first
- `docs/ai/reference/sitecore-rules.md` — canonical Sitecore rules reference
- `docs/ai/skills/shared/react-uiim-guidelines.md` — component patterns
- `docs/ai/reference/sitecore-marketer-mcp-reference.md` — MCP tool behaviors

## For other starters (article-starter, product-listing, skate-park)

These starters use the standard XM Cloud component patterns:

- SDK: `@sitecore-content-sdk/nextjs` (NOT `@sitecore-jss/sitecore-jss-nextjs`)
- Props: extend `ComponentProps` from `@/lib/component-props`
- Fields: use SDK editable helpers (`Text`, `RichText`, `NextImage`, `Link`)
- Variants: use named exports (`export const Default`, not `export default`)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui from `@/components/ui/*`
- Edit mode: `page.mode.isEditing` from `useSitecore()` hook
- Datasource: check `fields?.data?.datasource` existence, use `NoDataFallback` fallback
